    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Erasmus of Rotterdam to Miklós Oláh (Freiburg im Breisgau, 7
                    November 1533)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. Oláh is recommending to his attention the bearer of
                            this letter, Zuichemus, who used to teach law in Padua; he is a true
                            gem! He would like him to get to know him. 2. They say the church in
                            Antwerp has burned down, and that smaller towns have also burned down
                            around Cologne, and it is rumored that the city that is one day’s travel
                            away was set on fire by a demon. Dantyszek writes that the cathedral of
                            Chełmno has also burned down. They are also saying that Henry VIII would
                            take Catherine back, if only it was true, but he does not believe it is.
                            There is no change concerning his trip.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="15331107_1_1.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Erasmus Roterodamus Nicolao Olao thesaurario Albensi etc.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Utinam aula vestra tales amplectatur, qualis hic est
                        <persName>Viglius Schvichemius</persName>,<note xml:id="note.1">Wigle Aytta
                        or Viglius Zuichemus (1507–1577) studied at the University of Leuven, where
                        he read Latin and Greek authors with Wackers and Ressen. In 1532, he held
                        lectures in law at the University of Padua. More see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Erbe</hi> 1987b.</note> qui has<note xml:id="note.2">sc. <hi
                            rend="italic">epistolas</hi> or <hi rend="italic">litteras</hi>.</note>
                    reddit, iuvenis ingenio niveo, doctor iuris, qui
                        <placeName>Patavii</placeName><note xml:id="note.3">Padova.</note> publice
                    professus est, ut non sine certamine, ita non absque gloria. Nec seipso inferior
                    est in bonis litteris. Animo nulla gemma purior. Qui nulla commendatione digni
                    sunt, extorquent multas commendationes. Hic non postulavit vel uno verbo
                    commendari. Tantum hoc mea causa rogo, ut iuvenem tot ornamentis insignem velis
                    cognoscere.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Scribunt <placeName>Antverpiae</placeName> templum summum
                    deflagrasse. Quid sibi volunt tot incendia? Scribunt circa <placeName>Coloniam
                        Agrippinam</placeName><note xml:id="note.4">Cologne.</note> exusta oppidula.
                    Oppidum, quod hinc abest iter diei totum, conflagravit <choice>
                        <orig>igni</orig>
                        <supplied>igne</supplied>
                    </choice> a daemone immisso, ut constans est rumor. Narrant etiam in
                        <placeName>Helvetia</placeName> pagos aliquot conflagrasse.
                        <persName>Ioannes Dantiscus</persName><note xml:id="note.5">Jan
                        Dantyszek.</note> Culmensis episcopus scribit<note xml:id="note.6">See <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Skolimowska-Turska</hi> 2010, IDL 2012 Note 4.</note>
                    exustum <placeName>Culmum</placeName><note xml:id="note.7">Chełmża.</note>
                    civitatem cathedralem, insuper aliud oppidum,<note xml:id="note.8">Schiltach,
                        see <hi rend="smallcap">Allen</hi> 1941, 316.</note> ubi habebat arcem, sic
                    absumptum incendio, ut praeter maenia fere nihil supersit. Haec mihi videntur
                    omnino geri casu. Rumor hic est <persName>regem Angliae</persName> in pristinum
                    contubernium recepisse <persName>Catharinam</persName><note xml:id="note.9"
                        >Catherine of Aragon, the first wife of King Henry VIII. In fact, their
                        marriage was declared invalid this year, so this rumour was false.</note>
                    suam. Quod ut vix credibile videtur, ita cuperem esse verissimum. De proposito
                    reditus a nobis nihil est immutatum, nisi si quid interim istic exstiterit novi.
                    Rogo, ut tuum in me animum obtineas ac reginae favorem alas.
                        <persName>Dano</persName><note xml:id="note.10">Jakob Jespersen.</note> et
                        <persName>Levino</persName><note xml:id="note.11">Lieven Algoet.</note>
                    salutem. Vale.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Friburgi</placeName> 7. die Novembris 1533.</p>
            </div>
